<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
This taxon described by X. Montrouzier was completely forgotten and cited as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lam" authorityYear="1797" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Mollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the treatments of the New Caledonian flora (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Guillaumin, A" journalOrPublisher="Engelmann, Lipsiae" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="B7" refString="Guillaumin, A, 1948. Flore analytique et synoptique de la Nouvelle-Caledonie phanerogames." title="Flore analytique et synoptique de la Nouvelle-Caledonie phanerogames" year="1948">Guillaumin 1948</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rageau, J" journalOrPublisher="ORSTOM, Paris" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="1 - 138" refId="B14" refString="Rageau, J, 1973. Les plantes medicinales de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. ORSTOM, Paris: 1 - 138" title="Les plantes medicinales de la Nouvelle-Caledonie" year="1973">Rageau 1973</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized by unique reniform or even triangular leaf blades (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Paramollugo digyna. A general habit B leaf rosette C flower D inflorescence. Photographs by Julien Barrault." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.73.10365.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/107531" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">7</figureCitation>
), and by a tendency to become a short-lived perennial (in contrast to annual 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Unfortunately, many specimens were collected without the basal portion or in their first growing season, and it is still unclear which life form is predominant in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Neither perennial habit nor unusual leaf shape were mentioned in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Montrouzier, X" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="173 - 254" refId="B13" refString="Montrouzier, X, 1860. Flore de l'ile Art (pres de la Nouvelle Caledonie). Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts 10: 173 - 254" title="Flore de l'ile Art (pres de la Nouvelle Caledonie)." volume="10" year="1860">Montrouzier 1860</bibRefCitation>
), but the author indicated the presence of two-valved capsules. We also found that the specimens collected in New Caledonia have two- or rarely three-valved capsules with 8 or fewer seeds, in contrast to other herbaceous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M.Thulin" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are characterized by capsules with three locules and up to 30 seeds. The outer walls of the testa cells are elongated, almost rectangular, with secondary warty outgrowths. A similar seed surface was observed in the Caribbean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Ekman" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo navassensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="navassensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo navassensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is clearly distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Israel Journal of Plant Sciences" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" publicationUrl="10.1080/07929978.2016.1249137" refId="B16" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, Kushunina, M, in press. Taxonomic significance of seed morphology in the genus Mollugo s.l. (Molluginaceae). Israel Journal of Plant Sciences 164, DOI: 10.1080/07929978.2016.1249137" title="Taxonomic significance of seed morphology in the genus Mollugo s. l. (Molluginaceae)." url="10.1080/07929978.2016.1249137" volume="164" year="in press">Sukhorukov and Kushunina in press</bibRefCitation>
, sub 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Mollugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
