<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
No original material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was traced. The herbarium of X. Montrouzier, who described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Mollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is located in University of Montpellier herbarium (MPU), with some duplicates in the National Museum of Natural History, Paris (P). Only one specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found, without a precise location (MPU-310526). No specimens are cited in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Montrouzier, X" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="173 - 254" refId="B13" refString="Montrouzier, X, 1860. Flore de l'ile Art (pres de la Nouvelle Caledonie). Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts 10: 173 - 254" title="Flore de l'ile Art (pres de la Nouvelle Caledonie)." volume="10" year="1860">Montrouzier 1860</bibRefCitation>
). The sheet found in MPU (no. 169) and dated 1866 might have been collected later, and hence cannot be considered as original material. However, the plant clearly originates from New Caledonia due to the writing on the sheet &quot;Stylos binos semper, capsulamque bivalvam vidi!&quot; (&quot;stylodia always two, capsule two-valved&quot;). Since the original material is not found (Art. 9.16 of ICN) here we select a neotype that bears a plant with perennial life form, reniform leaves and two-valved capsules as the most indicative characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Sukhorukov &amp; Kushunina" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo digyna" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from New Caledonia where it usually grows on rocky or stony substrates; locally common (
<bibRefCitation author="Guillaumin, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal d'agriculture traditionnelle et de botanique appliquee" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="91 - 103" publicationUrl="10.3406/jatba.1964.2758" refId="B8" refString="Guillaumin, A, 1964. Contributions a la flore de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. CXXII. Plantes recoltees par M. Mackee (Suite). Journal d'agriculture traditionnelle et de botanique appliquee 11 (4): 91 - 103, DOI: 10.3406/jatba.1964.2758" title="Contributions a la flore de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. CXXII. Plantes recoltees par M. Mackee (Suite)." url="10.3406/jatba.1964.2758" volume="11" year="1964">Guillaumin 1964</bibRefCitation>
sub 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lam" authorityYear="1797" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Mollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Paramollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. is not present in New Caledonia.
</paragraph>
